import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['open'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'open' prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
